{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> σφάζω</b>, <br /> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 4.320, 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 2.39, 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Troades” 134 (Lyric poetry); in Comedy texts (5th c.BC: Cratinus Comicus 361) and Prose, from 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus (“Grg.” 468c)\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>] downwards, <b>σφάττω</b>, compare Σφαττόμενος title of play by [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-3rd c.BC: Diphilus Comicus, “IG” 22.2363.34, and ς[φά]ττετ[αι] “SIG” 1024.36 (Myconus, 3rd-2nd c.BC)\">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; <i>Boeotian dialect</i> <b>σφάδδω</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “Anecdota Graeca - MSS. Bibl. Oxon.” 4.325\">Refs</a>]: <i>future</i> σφάξω [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Heraclidae” 493 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: <i>aorist</i> ἔσφαξα [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 2.422: \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]<i>perfect</i> ἔσφᾰκα, known from <i>pluperfect</i> ἐσφάκειν [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd-3rd c.AD: Dio Cassius Historicus 73.6, (ἀπο-) 78.7 \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]:—<i>passive</i>, <i>future</i> σφᾰγήσομαι [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Andromache” 315, “Heracl.” 583, (ἀπο-) 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Historia Graeca (Hellenica)” 3.1.27: \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<i>aorist</i> ἐσφάγην [ᾰ] Trag. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\"(4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Eumenides” 305, etc.) and late Prose, 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus “Publicola” 4, etc.\">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; less frequently ἐσφάχθην, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “P.” 11.23, 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 5.5, 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Iphigenia Taurica” 177 (Lyric poetry, nowhere else in Trag.)\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: <i>perfect</i> ἔσφαγμαι [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 10.532, 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 23.68 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]:—<b>slay, slaughter</b>, properly <b>by cutting the throat</b> (see. σφαγή 11)[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\", in 8th c.BC: Homerus Epicus \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>] always of cattle, μῆλ᾽ ἁδινὰ σφάζουσι καὶ εἰλίποδας ἕλικας βοῦς [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 1.92, compare 9.46, 23.305, 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 9.467. \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> especially <b>slaughter</b> victims for sacrifice, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1.459 \">Refs</a>], etc.; ἔσφαζ᾽ ἐπ᾽ ὤμων μόσχον <b>cut</b> its <b>throat</b>, as it hung from the servant's shoulders, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Electra” 813; σ. παρθένου δέρην [prev. author] “Or.” 1199 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]:—<i>passive</i>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 10.532; ἀρνίον ἐσφαγμένον NT.Rev.5.6. \">NT+8th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.2</b></Level3> generally, <b>slay, kill</b>, of human victims, as Iphigeneia, Menoeceus, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “P.” 11.23, 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Phoenissae” 913, compare 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Agamemnon” 1433, “Ch.” 904 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; σ. τινὰ ἐς τὸν κρητῆρα so that the blood ran into the bowl, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 3.11 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]:— <i>passive</i>, σφάζεται ἐς τὸν τάφον [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] 5.5; πρὸς βωμῷ σφαγείς 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Eumenides” 305. \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.3</b></Level3> of any slaughter by knife or sword, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 5.25, 7.107; σ. ἑαυτόν 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 2.92; σ. καὶ ἐκδέρειν 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Euthydemus” 301c; τὸν ἴδιον ἀδελφόν “PMag.Osl.” 1.5, cf. NT.1John.3.12. \">NT+5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.4</b></Level3> of animals, <b>tear by the throat</b>, σ. ὥσπερ οἱ λύκοι τὰ πρόβατα [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Historia Animalium” 612b2. \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.5</b></Level3> of any killing, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “BGU” 388 ii 21 (2nd c.AD), “OGI” 697 (from Egypt), “Sammelb.” 7436.7 (6th c.AD), “Corpus Glossariorum Latinorum” \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.6</b></Level3> <i>metaphorically</i>, <b>torment</b>, τινα [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “POxy.” 259.33 (1st c.AD). \">Refs 1st c.AD+</a>]","strongNumber":"G4969","accentedUnicode":"σφάζω","relatedNos":[{"strongNumber":"G2695","matchingForm":"κατασφάζω","stepTransliteration":"katasfazō","gloss":"to slaughter","_zh_tw_Gloss":"殺了","_es_Gloss":"matar","_zh_Gloss":"杀了"},{"strongNumber":"G4967","matchingForm":"σφαγή","stepTransliteration":"sfagē","gloss":"slaughter","_zh_tw_Gloss":"宰殺","_es_Gloss":"muerte","_zh_Gloss":"宰杀"},{"strongNumber":"G4968","matchingForm":"σφάγιον","stepTransliteration":"sfagion","gloss":"sacrificial victim","_zh_tw_Gloss":"將犧牲","_es_Gloss":"víctima sacrificial","_zh_Gloss":"将牺牲"}],"shortDef":"to kill, slay, murder","mediumDef":"to kill, slay, murder <br />also spelled <greek>σφάττω</greek>, <b>to slaughter, kill, slay;</b>  <i>primarily</i> used of animals killed in sacrifice, etc., <ref='Rev.5.6, 9, 12; 13.8'>Rev. 5:6, 9, 12; 13:8</ref>; of persons, etc., <ref='1Jn.3.12'>1Jn. 3:12;</ref> <ref='Rev.6.4, 9; 18.24'>Rev. 6:4, 9; 18:24</ref>; <b>to wound mortally,</b> <ref='Rev.13.3'>Rev. 13:3</ref>*","stepGloss":"to slaughter","stepTransliteration":"sfazō","count":10,"_es_Definition":"herir de muerte, matar, asesinar ; herida de muerte (APOC.13:3)","_zh_tw_Definition":"屠殺","_zh_Definition":"屠杀","_step_Type":"verb","_vi_Definition":"giết; bị xử tử / giết bằng bạo lực","_z